07820.mean:
renowned martyr who reinvented and was dedicated to the development of the Kirant Limbu language and alphabet. Born in A.D. 1704 on the full moon day of Mangsir (Nov-Dec) at Sinam of Taplejung district in the eastern part of the modern Nepal. He is regarded as the re-incarnation of Sirijunga I. He was assassinated at Martam village of West Sikkim in A.D. 1741 in Rapdenchi Pemayonchi Monastery, by the conspiring Thachhang Lamas who were converting the Limbus to Buddhism. He is at present renowned as Sirijunga II.
